# Module `content.md` enrichment

Each module’s front matter may include (keep `id`, `title`, `summary`, `sensitivity`):

- **`sales_trio_guidelines_only`**: optional boolean for **sales-trio** modules (`sales-rules-of-engagement`, `sales-process-and-salesforce`, `sales-operations-and-approvals`). When `true`, the page renders **only** **Key Guidelines** and **Common Pitfalls** as the two tabs—no Overview tab and no **Process Deep Dive** block. Still keep `## Overview` and `## Process Deep Dive [deep]` in the markdown if you want commented or latent content for later. See `sales-process-and-salesforce`.

- **`sales_trio_hide_overview`**: optional boolean for **sales-trio** modules that use the default four-block layout (Overview + tabs + **Process Deep Dive**). When `true`, the **Overview** tab is omitted and its markdown is kept in the page **hidden** (redundant with **Coffee Summary**); **Key Guidelines** and **Common Pitfalls** still render as the two tabs, and **Process Deep Dive** is unchanged. See `sales-rules-of-engagement`.

- **`sales_trio_hide_deep_dive`**: optional boolean for the same four-block layout. When `true`, **Process Deep Dive [deep]** is omitted from the visible UI and its markdown is kept **hidden** in the DOM (e.g. training cards + **Module Reference Files** already carry the story). See `sales-operations-and-approvals`.

- **`reference_files`**: list of `{ label, sharepoint_url }` for SharePoint docs (open in new tab). Use `reference_files: []` until links exist; empty list shows a placeholder in **Module Reference Files** above **Scenarios**.
- **`video_sections`**: optional list of training **cards** after Coffee Summary. Each entry: `heading` (required), optional `intro` (plain text), optional `items` (same as legacy carousel: `title`, `src`, optional `poster`), optional `body` (markdown) for text-only cards or prose above a carousel. Use multiple entries for separate carousels (e.g. 101 vs GPC). See `sales-process-and-salesforce`. Headings whose text matches **Check In** or **Live session** (wording flexible) get a centered Microsoft Teams SVG watermark (`assets/brand/microsoft-teams-mark.svg`), sized to the card height with padding (`inset-6` / `md:inset-8`).
- **`video_carousel`** / **`video_carousel_intro`**: legacy single card **“Training videos”**; same `src`/`poster` rules as above. Prefer `video_sections` when you need more than one block. `product-uc-voice-and-collaboration` still uses this shape.
- **`five_minute_summary`**: block scalar (`|`) with short markdown bullets; the app shows this block under the heading **Coffee Summary**.
- **`five_minute_flow`**: optional horizontal stepper above the summary bullets. `aria_label` (optional) and `steps`: list of `title` (short label) and optional `caption` (one short line). Step text is shown in **title style** (word-start capitals; acronyms unchanged). Equal-width flex cells, prominent chevrons between. Pair with shorter bullets instead of a long “onboarding flow” paragraph (see `sales-process-and-salesforce`).
- **`your_coaches`**: optional; `heading` (default “Your Coaches”) and `coaches`: list of `name`, `email`, optional `role`, optional `photo` (`assets/training/salesforce/coaches/<slug>.png` etc.). Renders below Coffee Summary; missing `photo` uses a circular placeholder.
- **`knowledge_checks`**: list of objects with `question`, `options` (3 strings), `correct_index` (0-based), `explanation` (plain text).
- **`scenarios`**: list of objects with `title`, `situation` (`|` markdown), `choices` with `label` and `feedback` (strings; feedback can use light markdown).

Render order: full-width **header** → **Coffee Summary** + optional **`your_coaches`** + **`video_sections` / legacy `video_carousel` cards** + **`##` section cards** + **knowledge checks** (carousel + score, end of main column, ~70% on large screens) → **Module Reference Files** (top of right rail when `reference_files` is present) + **Scenarios** (scrollable below). Omit `reference_files` entirely to hide the reference block. Scenarios show **progress** (N/M reviewed), **selected-choice styling**, **Feedback** panels, **Reviewed** badge, and an **all complete** banner when every scenario has a choice. Target **~10** `knowledge_checks` per module. Invalid YAML breaks the admin preview and push validation.

Module slugs (see `modules-manifest.json`): `sales-rules-of-engagement`, `sales-process-and-salesforce`, `sales-operations-and-approvals`, `portfolio-and-business-capabilities`, `product-connectivity`, `product-security-and-sd-wan`, `product-cloud-wifi-and-backup`, `product-uc-voice-and-collaboration`, `competitive-positioning`.
